---

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and quarter @button mushrooms{4%ounce}(trimmed and quartered) (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!).

Open package of @chopped chicken breast{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pot{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook, stirring frequently, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat, transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pot.

Heat a drizzle of oil in the large pot over medium heat. Add mushrooms and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

While mushrooms cook, peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}(minced).

Use pot used for chicken here.

Stir @butter{1%tbsp} and garlic into pot with mushrooms; cook, stirring constantly, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @veggie stock concentrate{3}, @Israeli pearl pasta{2.5%ounce}, @cannellini beans{1%can} and their liquid, and 2 cups water (4 cups for 4). Bring to a boil, then reduce to a low simmer. Stir in @spinach{5%ounce}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until spinach is wilted and flavors meld, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Once spinach is wilted and flavors meld, add chicken to soup.

Divide soup between #bowls{} and top with @Italian cheese blend{1/2%cup}. Sprinkle with as many @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} as you like. Serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.